    <title>more window patterns in gsp</title>
    <content type='html'>&lt;div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"&gt;
&lt;a href="https://blogger.googleusercontent.com/img/b/R29vZ2xl/AVvXsEgYgRrqZKCs9unpgKve0IPvkRcZnnp5MJSTg42i8p8JZ4hcYET__cgzYuqcr4aSZD1b8S-hDmFMucflccUw0_SPd6SdojHQwiP9JXFOPQOI3EhUASS-ud2WQZKvdlcd905o78CBuUel9Z4/s1600/squares-into-saw-45.JPG" imageanchor="1" style="margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em;"&gt;&lt;img border="0" height="320" src="https://blogger.googleusercontent.com/img/b/R29vZ2xl/AVvXsEgYgRrqZKCs9unpgKve0IPvkRcZnnp5MJSTg42i8p8JZ4hcYET__cgzYuqcr4aSZD1b8S-hDmFMucflccUw0_SPd6SdojHQwiP9JXFOPQOI3EhUASS-ud2WQZKvdlcd905o78CBuUel9Z4/s320/squares-into-saw-45.JPG" width="320" /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
You'd be right in saying 'hey, these are just a bunch of overlapping squares.' Yes. The only redeeming thing that I can point to is that they are made by following a rule, and the rule is one that is easy to reproduce without using any external measuring device (like a ruler or protractor), only the squares themselves. Think origami: you find midpoints by folding, etc. In this case, GSP is used, but only simple constructions like mid-point finding and segment creating. &lt;br /&gt;
&lt;div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"&gt;
&lt;a href="https://blogger.googleusercontent.com/img/b/R29vZ2xl/AVvXsEgnpuXwZtkc0GFKQE6t8T5KqaAy7Fog6_iJSS8ywTspSQM2yFysbgwe3fZx-pFlfO7x4QWQ9_4KyjeAR-KBYfGtw2BEQCTvjhpv07vDUVDQzZ2TuqcPWovlweExFLVvrMkN3fleVGWt7e0/s1600/another-hexagon-wp.JPG" imageanchor="1" style="margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em;"&gt;&lt;img border="0" height="320" src="https://blogger.googleusercontent.com/img/b/R29vZ2xl/AVvXsEgnpuXwZtkc0GFKQE6t8T5KqaAy7Fog6_iJSS8ywTspSQM2yFysbgwe3fZx-pFlfO7x4QWQ9_4KyjeAR-KBYfGtw2BEQCTvjhpv07vDUVDQzZ2TuqcPWovlweExFLVvrMkN3fleVGWt7e0/s320/another-hexagon-wp.JPG" width="316" /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
The trick is to find a rule that allows you to start with a square and then construct two points that you can base another square on, and then repeat.&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"&gt;
&lt;a href="https://blogger.googleusercontent.com/img/b/R29vZ2xl/AVvXsEgw7QdXIQ3j53lc5A9Qis7ApcyBdcrS9BXz96nfK84KvXjHaobQFpgmFGMltqrpaUgwTJDe3PjZTjSwAp8pnggBhZlAX4IM5dt8_fNrgZ2E0Eik7A5IPJeSgBwSWE16wHFHv-tEXMRhuCI/s1600/anothergon.JPG" imageanchor="1" style="margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em;"&gt;&lt;img border="0" height="302" src="https://blogger.googleusercontent.com/img/b/R29vZ2xl/AVvXsEgw7QdXIQ3j53lc5A9Qis7ApcyBdcrS9BXz96nfK84KvXjHaobQFpgmFGMltqrpaUgwTJDe3PjZTjSwAp8pnggBhZlAX4IM5dt8_fNrgZ2E0Eik7A5IPJeSgBwSWE16wHFHv-tEXMRhuCI/s320/anothergon.JPG" width="320" /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
